analysis: The documents primarily concern adjustments to the rates of pay and allowances for various categories of federal employees, including those in the General Schedule, Foreign Service, Veterans Health Administration, Senior Executive Service, uniformed services, and executive, legislative, and judicial branches. The adjustments are made to comply with existing laws and are typically effective at the beginning of the first applicable pay period or on specific dates like January 1st or October 1st of a given year. Many of the orders supersede previous executive orders related to pay adjustments.
title: Federal Employee Compensation Updates
